Renault to Hire Formula One’s First Female Driver in 20 Years, AS Reports

-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 
2011-11-30T16:53:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-30/renault-to-hire-formula-one-s-first-female-driver-in-20-years-as-reports.html
The Lotus Renault Formula One team
agreed to hire Maria de Villota as a reserve driver for next
year’s championship, As newspaper reported, citing an interview
with the 31-year-old Spaniard.  De Villota said “it’s just a question of signing the
contract,” according to the newspaper. The last woman to drive
at a Grand Prix weekend was  Italy ’s Giovanna Amati, who failed
to qualify for three races for the Brabham team in 1992.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alex Duff at 
 aduff4@bloomberg.net  